        "## 17.15 Diagnostics after machine learning\n",
        "\n",
        "A flexible ML model can fit nonlinear patterns, but it can still leave time-dependent errors. Let\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "e_{t,h}=Y_{t+h}-\\widehat Y_{t+h\\mid t}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Useful diagnostics include:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. time plot of forecast errors;\n",
        "2. ACF of forecast errors;\n",
        "3. error versus fitted value;\n",
        "4. error by horizon;\n",
        "5. error by calendar group;\n",
        "6. comparison with naive and seasonal naive baselines;\n",
        "7. performance during regime changes or shock periods.\n",
        "\n",
